During a flight to Pennsylvania, White House spokesperson Karine Jean-Pierre discussed President Biden's proposed Buy American rule, which aims to support American workers and businesses. The President will visit the Lehigh Valley Operations manufacturing facility for Mack Trucks and receive a briefing on the company's electric dump truck. Jean-Pierre also mentioned the launch of a new rental assistance finder by the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, which helps Americans who are behind on their rent. Regarding vaccine mandates for federal employees, Jean-Pierre stated that attestation of vaccination or abiding by COVID-19 protocols is under consideration. She also addressed concerns about mask mandates exacerbating divisions in the United States, emphasizing that the CDC guidance is based on public health experts' recommendations to save lives.